{{Han compound|扌|戈|c1=s|c2=p|ls=psc}}.

Originally a variant form of {{zh-l|*划}}. Borrowed to mean a similar action.{{rfv-etymology|zh}}

The popular interpretation as a hand ({{zh-l|*扌}}) looking for an halberd ({{zh-l|*戈}}) is a [[mnemonic]] and not the etymology of the character.
===Etymology 1===
Both “seek” and “give change” senses are attested since the Ming dynasty. The etymology is uncertain and it is unclear whether both senses are of the same origin. Compare {{zh-l|爪}} and {{zh-l|抓}}.

